/2021/02/GettyImages-1304362550-910x597.jpg 910w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" data-recalc-dims="1"> An interesting narrative in the midfield has been hidden beneath the importance of the picture. In 2016 Bayern Munich acquired the services of the highly rated central midfielder Renato Sanches. Despite the hype, Sanches could not quite earn his way into the team and was eventually sent out on loan to Swansea City where he failed again to impress. Meanwhile in the same year Bayern brought in Corentin Tolisso from Lyon. The Frenchman achieved what Sanches could not and effectively took his place in the squad. Eventually in 2019 Sanches left for Lille. Winning the title last season, Sanches re-established himself as one of Europe’s most appreciated prospects. <img class="alignnone wp-image-734031 size-large lazyload" title="SWANSEA, WALES - SEPTEMBER 10: Renato Sanches of Swansea City and Jesus Gamez of Newcastle United in action during the Premier League match between Swansea City and Newcastle United at Liberty Stadium on September 10, 2017 in Swansea, Wales. (Photo by Stu Forster/Getty Images)" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" data-src="https://www.101greatgoals.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/GettyImages-845281004-1024x686.jpg" alt="Portugal vs France: Context, H2H, key battles, subplots &amp; predicted line-ups" width="1024" height="686" data-srcset="https://www.101greatgoals.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/GettyImages-845281004.jpg 1024w, https://www.101greatgoals.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/GettyImages-845281004-300x201.jpg 300w, https://www.101greatgoals.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/GettyImages-845281004-768x515.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"><img class="alignnone wp-image-734031 size-large lazyload jetpack-lazy-image" title="SWANSEA, WALES - SEPTEMBER 10: Renato Sanches of Swansea City and Jesus Gamez of Newcastle United in action during the Premier League match between Sw